21/24224084/google-pixel-9-reimagine-ai-photos", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google\u2019s AI \u2018Reimagine\u2019 tool helped us add wrecks, disasters, and corpses to our photos", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-21T09:47:05+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of a photo of the US Capitol building with an image of the Constitution behind it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CyWXhFBGdUB5DogOYK0CqasdCcg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73534295/STK481_STK432_CONGRESS_GOVERNMENT_CIVRGINIA_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge; Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZVT8G5\">A federal judge has blocked the Federal Trade Commission\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/23/24138559/ftc-noncompete-agreement-ban\">ban on noncompete agreements</a> that make it difficult for workers to join their employers\u2019 rivals or launch competing businesses. The ruling prevents the FTC\u2019s ban on noncompete agreements from taking effect on September 4th, though the agency could still appeal the decision.</p>\n<p id=\"eqgvb6\">On Tuesday, US District Judge Ada Brown in Dallas, Texas <a href=\"https://storage.courtlistener.com/recap/gov.uscourts.txnd.389", "id": 1036129, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/21/24225112/ftc-noncompete-agreement-ban-blocked-judge", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The FTC\u2019s noncompete agreements ban has been struck down", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-21T09:32:21+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a pixelated key next to a padlock and chain, implying online data security.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/t3a4j7abTL03-jpw5x78ZM85O4Q=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73534293/STK453_Privacy_D_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photo: Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"YMtiY9\">Microsoft\u2019s latest monthly security update is wreaking havoc on dual-boot Windows and Linux systems. The software giant issued a security patch last week to fix a two-year-old vulnerability in the GRUB open-source boot loader used by lots of Linux devices. Microsoft\u2019s patch wasn\u2019t supposed to hit dual-boot devices, but many have found it has and it\u2019s now stopping their Linux installs from booting properly.</p>\n<p id=\"Sf1Vr8\"><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/security/2024/08/a-patch-microsoft-spent-2-years-preparing-is-making-a-mess-for-some-linux-users/\"><em>Ars Technica </em>report", "id": 1036130, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/21/24225108/microsoft-security-update-windows-linux-dual-boot-errors", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u2019s latest security update has ruined dual-boot Windows and Linux PCs", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-08-21T09:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n 